{"type":"message","id":"ab75e6c2","parentId":"1e052aa7","timestamp":"2026-03-02T03:24:54.513Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good question — it's a safety boundary. My default workspace is `/Users/hope/.openclaw/agents/main/workspace`, and I can only directly read/write files inside that folder to prevent accidental changes elsewhere.\n\nBut don't worry: I *can* still operate on `/Users/hope/IdeaProjects` using shell commands (like `echo`, `cp`, `git`, etc.) via the `exec` tool, which runs in your real user environment. So while I can't *directly* write there with the `write` tool, I can absolutely create or modify files there through the terminal.\n\nWant me to create that test file now using `exec`?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3-max-2026-01-23","usage":{"input":13660,"output":137,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13797,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772421886980}}
