{"type":"message","id":"0ca4d2d5","parentId":"66d2f685","timestamp":"2026-03-02T03:25:27.775Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You can adjust OpenClaw's file access policy by modifying the **`fileAccess`** setting in your agent's configuration.\n\nBy default, agents run in a restricted mode (`fileAccess: \"workspace\"`) for safety. To allow full filesystem access (so tools like `write`, `read`, and `edit` work anywhere), you need to set:\n\n```json\n\"fileAccess\": \"full\"\n```\n\n### How to change it:\n1. Locate your agent config — likely at:  \n   `/Users/hope/.openclaw/agents/main/config.json`\n2. Add or update the `fileAccess` field:\n   ```json\n   {\n     \"fileAccess\": \"full\",\n     // ... other settings\n   }\n   ```\n3. Restart the agent (or reload the session).\n\n⚠️ **Warning**: This grants the agent full read/write access to your entire filesystem. Only do this if you trust the agent and understand the risks.\n\nWould you like me to check your current config or help modify it?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3-max-2026-01-23","usage":{"input":13848,"output":209,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14057,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772421919702}}
