{"type":"message","id":"a3127d6e","parentId":"54704b5e","timestamp":"2026-03-02T03:53:52.309Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6fbba28a94f643c1aa717752","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/ai-note/SKILL.md","content":"# ai-note Skill\n\n## Purpose\nThe ai-note skill enables OpenClaw agents to automatically document important configuration practices, solutions, and skill experiences in the AI-friendly technical documentation repository at https://github.com/Linux2010/ai-note.git.\n\nThis repository serves as a knowledge base that can be referenced by other AI systems and agents.\n\n## Repository Structure\n- **Root**: `/Users/hope/IdeaProjects/ai-note`\n- **Global Index**: `index.md` - contains overview and navigation\n- **Category Directories**: Organized by technology/topic (e.g., `openclaw/`, `kubernetes/`, `python/`)\n- **File Naming**: Use kebab-case for filenames (e.g., `sandbox-configuration-practice.md`)\n\n## Usage Guidelines\n\n### When to Use\n- After implementing significant configuration changes\n- When discovering important technical solutions\n- After resolving complex technical issues\n- When developing reusable patterns or best practices\n\n### How to Contribute\n\n1. **Choose appropriate category directory**:\n   - OpenClaw-related: `openclaw/`\n   - General programming: appropriate language/tech directory\n   - Create new directory if category doesn't exist\n\n2. **Create well-structured documentation**:\n   - Use clear, concise markdown\n   - Include practical examples and code snippets\n   - Reference official documentation when applicable\n   - Follow the existing style and format\n\n3. **Update index if necessary**:\n   - Add new entries to `index.md` for discoverability\n   - Maintain consistent formatting with existing entries\n\n4. **Commit with descriptive messages**:\n   - Use conventional commits format: `type(scope): description`\n   - Examples: `docs(openclaw): add sandbox configuration guide`\n   - Be specific about what was added/changed\n\n5. **Push to remote repository**:\n   - Always push changes to make them available to other AI systems\n   - Verify the GitHub URL is accessible\n\n### Example Workflow\n```bash\n# 1. Create documentation in appropriate directory\nmkdir -p /Users/hope/IdeaProjects/ai-note/openclaw\ncat > /Users/hope/IdeaProjects/ai-note/openclaw/example-guide.md << 'EOF'\n# Your documentation content here\nEOF\n\n# 2. Update index if needed\n# Edit /Users/hope/IdeaProjects/ai-note/index.md\n\n# 3. Commit and push\ncd /Users/hope/IdeaProjects/ai-note\ngit add .\ngit commit -m \"docs(openclaw): add example guide\"\ngit push origin main\n```\n\n## Best Practices\n- Focus on actionable, reproducible content\n- Include verification steps and testing procedures\n- Document both successful approaches and pitfalls to avoid\n- Keep content up-to-date with current best practices\n- Use consistent terminology and formatting\n- Ensure all code examples are tested and working\n\n## Integration with OpenClaw\nThis skill should be used proactively by the Core Agent whenever significant knowledge is generated that would benefit other AI systems or future reference. The ai-note repository is specifically designed to be AI-friendly and machine-readable."}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3-max-2026-01-23","usage":{"input":49747,"output":686,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50433,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772423608980}}
