{"type":"message","id":"30827494","parentId":"258635c7","timestamp":"2026-03-02T06:15:36.019Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_52a7bbabf01748f0bc97e896","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"clawhub github api rate limit workaround\",\n  \"provider\": \"brave\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 850,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"brave\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"dfc50ce1ffc42c4a\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSecurity overview · openclaw/clawhub · GitHub\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"dfc50ce1ffc42c4a\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclaw/clawhub/security\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"853813537010c58f\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTo reduce rate-limit failures, <strong>set GITHUB_TOKEN in Convex env for authenticated GitHub API requests</strong>.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"853813537010c58f\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2f852634f6447385\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nFAQ - OpenClaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"2f852634f6447385\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://docs.openclaw.ai/help/faq\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0a404caabdc825a3\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n<strong>If you use a Claude subscription (setup-token or Claude Code OAuth), wait for the window to reset or upgrade your plan</strong>. If you use an Anthropic API key, check the Anthropic Console for usage/billing and raise limits as needed.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0a404caabdc825a3\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"docs.openclaw.ai\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"dbd3b16594777002\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nRate limit too aggressive + no visibility (no headers, no docs) · Issue #349 · openclaw/clawhub\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"dbd3b16594777002\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclaw/clawhub/issues/349\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"31a0c957073511fe\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n<strong>No visibility</strong> — Error is just &quot;Rate limit exceeded&quot;. No Retry-After header, no window size, no remaining quota, no reset time, no docs. Inconsistent — publish sometimes works when install is rate limited on the same token in the same minute.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"31a0c957073511fe\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"2 weeks ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9fa3010f848e462d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n[Bug]: OpenRouter API rate limit failover · Issue #1405 · openclaw/openclaw\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9fa3010f848e462d\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/1405\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3a7cbd4b03b6b044\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSteps to reproduce <strong>Configure Clawdbot with OpenRouter as a provider with a $5 spending limit</strong> Use the bot until the spending limit is hit (context starts returning empty due to rate limiting) Increase or remove the spending limit on OpenRouter ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3a7cbd4b03b6b044\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"January 21, 2026\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"edd880c7b0ded36f\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nr/openclaw on Reddit: API rate limit reached every time\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"edd880c7b0ded36f\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.reddit.com/r/openclaw/comments/1rc6l7x/api_rate_limit_reached_every_time/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"731e8d6bb6507c51\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nI also found when I blew a TPM limit the limit wouldn’t reset. As people have said have a fallback model that is cheap. I think using sub agents is the way to go and have the conversational model on a cheaper one. Some people have a local LLM for conversations then others running on sub agents. ... Yeah I started with Chatgpt API but I burned through $$$ quickly.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"731e8d6bb6507c51\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"1 week ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.reddit.com\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"clawhub github api rate limit workaround","provider":"brave","count":5,"tookMs":850,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"brave","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"dfc50ce1ffc42c4a\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSecurity overview · openclaw/clawhub · GitHub\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"dfc50ce1ffc42c4a\">>>","url":"https://github.com/openclaw/clawhub/security","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"853813537010c58f\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nTo reduce rate-limit failures, <strong>set GITHUB_TOKEN in Convex env for authenticated GitHub API requests</strong>.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"853813537010c58f\">>>","siteName":"github.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2f852634f6447385\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nFAQ - OpenClaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2f852634f6447385\">>>","url":"https://docs.openclaw.ai/help/faq","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0a404caabdc825a3\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n<strong>If you use a Claude subscription (setup-token or Claude Code OAuth), wait for the window to reset or upgrade your plan</strong>. If you use an Anthropic API key, check the Anthropic Console for usage/billing and raise limits as needed.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"0a404caabdc825a3\">>>","siteName":"docs.openclaw.ai"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"dbd3b16594777002\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nRate limit too aggressive + no visibility (no headers, no docs) · Issue #349 · openclaw/clawhub\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"dbd3b16594777002\">>>","url":"https://github.com/openclaw/clawhub/issues/349","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"31a0c957073511fe\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n<strong>No visibility</strong> — Error is just &quot;Rate limit exceeded&quot;. No Retry-After header, no window size, no remaining quota, no reset time, no docs. Inconsistent — publish sometimes works when install is rate limited on the same token in the same minute.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"31a0c957073511fe\">>>","published":"2 weeks ago","siteName":"github.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9fa3010f848e462d\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n[Bug]: OpenRouter API rate limit failover · Issue #1405 · openclaw/openclaw\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9fa3010f848e462d\">>>","url":"https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/1405","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3a7cbd4b03b6b044\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSteps to reproduce <strong>Configure Clawdbot with OpenRouter as a provider with a $5 spending limit</strong> Use the bot until the spending limit is hit (context starts returning empty due to rate limiting) Increase or remove the spending limit on OpenRouter ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3a7cbd4b03b6b044\">>>","published":"January 21, 2026","siteName":"github.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"edd880c7b0ded36f\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nr/openclaw on Reddit: API rate limit reached every time\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"edd880c7b0ded36f\">>>","url":"https://www.reddit.com/r/openclaw/comments/1rc6l7x/api_rate_limit_reached_every_time/","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"731e8d6bb6507c51\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nI also found when I blew a TPM limit the limit wouldn’t reset. As people have said have a fallback model that is cheap. I think using sub agents is the way to go and have the conversational model on a cheaper one. Some people have a local LLM for conversations then others running on sub agents. ... Yeah I started with Chatgpt API but I burned through $$$ quickly.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"731e8d6bb6507c51\">>>","published":"1 week ago","siteName":"www.reddit.com"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772432136010}}
{"type":"message","id":"2e614c24","parentId":"30827494","timestamp":"2026-03-02T06:15:59.242Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"从搜索结果看，这是一个已知问题。GitHub Issue #349 明确提到了 **\"Rate limit too aggressive + no visibility\"** 的问题。\n\n### 当前状况分析：\n1. **这是 ClawHub 服务端的问题**，不是你的配置问题\n2. **没有重试时间提示**，只能等待\n3. **社区已经报告了这个问题**\n\n### 建议的行动方案：\n\n**立即方案**：等待并重试\n- 等待 15-30 分钟后再试\n- GitHub API 限制通常会在 1 小时内重置\n\n**备用方案**：手动贡献到 GitHub\n- 既然这是 GitHub 贡献技能，可以直接提交到 OpenClaw 官方仓库\n- 创建 PR 到 `openclaw/skills` 仓库\n\n**长期方案**：联系 ClawHub 团队\n- 这个问题需要他们优化 API 使用策略\n\n让我先等待 15 分钟再尝试一次，同时准备手动贡献的备选方案。你希望我优先尝试哪种方式？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3-max-2026-01-23","usage":{"input":64990,"output":231,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65221,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772432136019}}
